                <div class="paragraphi"><p>I’m a designer from the UK, with a focus oscillating between systems, technologies and experiences for a more distributed, democratic and sustainable future. I try to adopt a <a id="mail" href="http://helsinkidesignlab.org/pages/what-is-strategic-design.html" target="_blank">strategic</a> and <a id="mail" href="http://www.designkit.org/human-centered-design" target="_blank">human-centred</a> approach to tackle systemic challenges through tangible products and user experiences.<p>I studied <a id="mail" href="https://www.rca.ac.uk/schools/school-of-design/design-products/" target="_blank">Design Products</a> at the Royal College of Art, where my work explored the Circular Economy and distributed low-carbon energy. Before this, I studied <a id="mail" href="https://www.ifm.eng.cam.ac.uk/education/met/" target="_blank">Manufacturing Engineering</a> at Cambridge University where I developed design guidelines for more easily repairable domestic appliances, in collaboration with Dualit and Dyson.</p><p>I’m currently working at <a id="mail" href="https://darkmatterlabs.org" target="_blank">Dark Matter Laboratories</a>, designing the institutional infrastructure for a decentralised, distributed and democratic tomorrow. I have previously worked in cleantech consulting at the <a id="mail" href="https://www.carbontrust.com/home/" target="_blank">Carbon Trust</a> as well as hands on design roles in a number of small design studios.</p><p>I am currently based in London.<br><a id="mail" href="mailto:mail@oliverburgess.uk">mail@oliverburgess.uk</a></p></div>
